title: For Sale/Trade:  HK P2000 With LEM Trigger
postcontent:
The P2000 is a short recoil-operated locked breech pistol with a modified Browning-type linkless cam action with a vertically tilting barrel also employed in the USP series of self-loading pistols, as well as most modern linkless semi autos.
The cold hammer-forged barrel has a polygonal profile while the slide is made from a solid bar of nitro-carburized steel. Following recent trends in modern pistol designs, the P2000 makes extensive use of impact-resistant polymers to reduce weight and production costs.
As with other recent Heckler & Koch pistol designs, the P2000 is modular to suit individual needs. For instance, the grip is modular with exchangeable backstraps to adjust to individual grips, allowing the user to customize the pistol's grip size. There is an interface for accessories built into the frame in front of the trigger guard; the universal accessory rail on the dust cover that allows for the use of tactical lights, laser pointers and other accessories. Attachment is positive and does not require any tools. This is in contrast with the USP series, which uses a proprietary H&K mounting rail that limits the types of accessories that could be used with the pistol.
The P2000 is a hammer-fired pistol with an exposed spurred hammer; a bobbed hammer is optional. It has ambidextrous slide locks and a fully ambidextrous magazine release installed in the trigger guard, on both sides. Various trigger and cocking systems offer the possibility of converting the trigger firing mode from one type to another. Several variants are available based whether the LEM (Law Enforcement Modification) trigger (H&K's double-action only) mechanism is used versus a SA/DA trigger. Comes with 3 mags,box, and manual. title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta M-92 SB Type "M" Compact
postcontent: A very scarce Italian made Beretta Model 92SB Compact Type M. Model # PO9219CM Single stack eight round 9mm with 4.25” barrel. Serial # dates it 1990. Original high polish blue finish is outstanding and looks great. Factory grips. Includes Beretta case and 3 factory eight round magazines. Only produced in limited quantities for export to the US, only about 1200 of this model were brought into the country in the late 1980’s and early 90’s. The SB line was the model prior to the 92F and offered high polish blue finish but with many of the standard features you see on 92’s today including ambi safety/decocker and thumb mag release. The single stack “Type M” offers a more compact profile versus the girth of a double stack magazine. This is a very collectible pistol and a similar model in stainless was brought back into production for a limited time a few years ago. A nice collector Beretta Model 92SB Compact Type M. This is a hard gun to find and I am firm on the price.
